    syllabusOutcomes: ["BIO12-5", "BIO12-6", "BIO12-7", "BIO12-12"],
    questionText: "Two graphs show the phenotype frequency ratios of offspring from crosses of pure-breeding parents. Graph A shows a 3:1 ratio. Graph B shows a 1:2:1 ratio. Using Punnett squares, explain the type of inheritance shown by each graph. Include a suitable key for each.",
    markingCriteria: "5 marks: Explains frequency ratios; Draws suitable Punnett squares for each trait; Links Punnett squares to frequency ratio and type of inheritance; Provides a suitable key\n4 marks: Identifies frequency ratios; Draws suitable Punnett squares for each trait; Provides a suitable key; Indicates both types of inheritance correctly\n3 marks: Identifies frequency ratio(s); Draws a suitable Punnett square; Indicates one type of inheritance correctly\n2 marks: Demonstrates understanding of a mode(s) of inheritance\n1 mark: Provides some relevant information",
